title: Suspicious Azure CommandLine
id: 2a3a051b-946a-442e-b3ff-def01db439a2
status: experimental
description: Detects suspicious AZ CommandLine from a windows host.  These commands ran in a short timeperiod should warrant investigation as Threat Actor could be performing Discovery.  
references:
    -   https://support.scythe.io/knowledge/azure-resource-group-backdoor    
author: Tyler Casey @1qazCasey, @scythe_io
date: 2024/03/28
tags:
    - attack.execution
    - attack.1059
    - attack.discovery
    - attack.1087.004
logsource:
    product: windows
    category: proc_creation
detection:
    selection:
        CommandLine|contains:
            - 'az vm run-command'
            - 'az vm show'
            - 'az network nic'
            - 'az network nsg'
            - 'az network public-ip'
            - 'az vm list'
    condition: selection
falsepositives:
    - Administrators may use this for Azure VM management.
level: 
    - medium